Genetic Algorithms, Probabilistic Methods. 

Genetic algorithms are present in the simulation research mentioned in the paper, where populations were simulated to study the effects of directional and non-directional mate preferences. 

Probabilistic methods are also present in the simulation framework presented in the paper, which allows for the simulation of a wide range of mate preferences. The paper discusses the use of probability distributions to model mate preferences and the effects of sexual selection on phenotype adaptation.
